title: Japanese-American Resettlement Through the Lens - Hikaru Iwasaki
description:
Japanese-American Resettlement Through the Lens: Hikaru Iwasaki and the WRA's Photographic Section, 1943-1945 By Lane Hirabayashi
UPC 2009 | 221 Pages | ISBN: 0870819283 | PDF | 12 MB

In Japanese American Resettlement through the Lens, Lane Ryo Hirabayashi gathers a unique collection of photographs by War Relocation Authority photographer Hikaru Iwasaki, the only full time WRA photographer from the period still living.
